'''OSETS 2711''' was an [[Orbital Solar Energy Transfer Satellite]] above the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]. It was placed under the command of [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Virar Needa]], though it was remotely commandeered by [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]] during their attempt to bring down the planet's shields. The Rogues focused the energy reflected from OSETS 2711 onto a water reservoir, boiling it and causing a series of huge thunderstorms that knocked out Coruscant's computer systems.<ref name="WG">''[[X-Wing: Wedge's Gamble]]''</ref>

It was subsequently used to focus sunlight toward one of the [[Golan III Space Defense NovaGun|Golan stations]] defending Coruscant, neutralizing the defense platform by burning a hole through the hull. Needa made no effort to stop the satellite from being used in this manner, hoping that the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] would treat him better than the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] did.<ref name="WG" />

The meticulous traffic observation logs kept by Lieutenant Needa later helped [[Iella Wessiri Antilles|Iella Wessiri]] in her search for the truth about Rogue [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] [[Corran Horn/Legends|Corran Horn's]] apparent death.<ref name="WG" />

